  "algorithm_summary": "This phenotype identifies steroid-induced osteonecrosis cases by requiring exposure to systemic corticosteroid medications (IV, IM, or PO routes only) while excluding patients with other known risk factors for osteonecrosis. The algorithm excludes patients with alcohol abuse, sickle cell disease, Gaucher disease, HIV (requiring 3+ codes), Legg-Calve-Perthes disease, or organ transplant history based on specific ICD-9 and CPT codes. It uses both structured data (medications, diagnoses) and NLP for case identification. The phenotype also considers PheWAS codes for conditions that are either indications for steroids or markers of steroid exposure to help validate cases and controls.",
